Text.SourceString: You’re from Pokyo, huh?//<portrait=normal>I came from a metropolitan area myself. The Big Apple… You’ve heard of it, I’m sure.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re from Pokyo, huh?//<portrait=normal>I came from a metropolitan area myself. The Big Apple… You’ve heard of it, I’m sure.

Text.SourceString: Anyhow, my name is <NPCName>Scott</>. Welcome to town!//Don’t be a stranger!
Text.LocalizedString: Anyhow, my name is <NPCName>Scott</>. Welcome to town!//Don’t be a stranger!

Text.SourceString: Oh man, you reminded me…//I need to drop off some trash at the recycling center today.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh man, you reminded me…//I need to drop off some trash at the recycling center today.

Text.SourceString: Wait, did I offend you? I meant it as a compliment.//<portrait=happy>You look like someone who recycles a lot, for some reason.
Text.LocalizedString: Wait, did I offend you? I meant it as a compliment.//<portrait=happy>You look like someone who recycles a lot, for some reason.

Text.SourceString: I found a couple of empty bottles in the forest yesterday.//<portrait=annoyed>How’d those get there?
Text.LocalizedString: I found a couple of empty bottles in the forest yesterday.//<portrait=annoyed>How’d those get there?

Text.SourceString: I brought the bottles and tossed them in the bin on my way home.
Text.LocalizedString: I brought the bottles and tossed them in the bin on my way home.

Text.SourceString: Last weekend I walked around town and had lunch on the empty plot of land next to <NpcName>Frank’s</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Last weekend I walked around town and had lunch on the empty plot of land next to <NpcName>Frank’s</>.

Text.SourceString: It was nice and quiet.//I could use more of that in my life.
Text.LocalizedString: It was nice and quiet.//I could use more of that in my life.

Text.SourceString: Time to get back to work.//<portrait=happy>Monday, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Time to get back to work.//<portrait=happy>Monday, huh?

Text.SourceString: We handle artifacts from the cavern and from the sea.//<portrait=normal>They require different approaches to clean.
Text.LocalizedString: We handle artifacts from the cavern and from the sea.//<portrait=normal>They require different approaches to clean.

Text.SourceString: I love my job.//We get to check out artifacts that have been around for hundreds of years.
Text.LocalizedString: I love my job.//We get to check out artifacts that have been around for hundreds of years.

Text.SourceString: Well… It’s not all old. Most of what we get turns out to be junk.//<portrait=normal>But it’s awesome when we get an artifact that’s both rare <Italic>and</> old.//Feels good to be part of the discovery.
Text.LocalizedString: Well… It’s not all old. Most of what we get turns out to be junk.//<portrait=normal>But it’s awesome when we get an artifact that’s both rare <Italic>and</> old.//Feels good to be part of the discovery.

Text.SourceString: What are you up to?//I don’t do much on Tuesdays and Wednesdays.//I usually just go to the museum and then right back to bed.
Text.LocalizedString: What are you up to?//I don’t do much on Tuesdays and Wednesdays.//I usually just go to the museum and then right back to bed.

Text.SourceString: One of those days, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: One of those days, you know?

Text.SourceString: I like to go to the Tavern to catch up with my crew on the weekend.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to go to the Tavern to catch up with my crew on the weekend.

Text.SourceString: I didn’t get to stretch this morning.//<portrait=annoyed>I feel my back tightening up.
Text.LocalizedString: I didn’t get to stretch this morning.//<portrait=annoyed>I feel my back tightening up.

Text.SourceString: I woke up too late again.//Maybe I’ll do some quick stretching later, after work.
Text.LocalizedString: I woke up too late again.//Maybe I’ll do some quick stretching later, after work.

Text.SourceString: I get woken up a lot by weird dreams.//It’s annoying, if you ask me.
Text.LocalizedString: I get woken up a lot by weird dreams.//It’s annoying, if you ask me.

Text.SourceString: I wake up tired, but I can’t ever remember anything. Huh.
Text.LocalizedString: I wake up tired, but I can’t ever remember anything. Huh.

Text.SourceString: You strike me as the type who reads every night before going to bed.//Am I right?
Text.LocalizedString: You strike me as the type who reads every night before going to bed.//Am I right?

Text.SourceString: I’m more the light-stretching-before-bed type.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m more the light-stretching-before-bed type.

Text.SourceString: I can’t wait to go to sleep tonight.//Worked out pretty hard this morning… Now I’m all fatigued.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wait to go to sleep tonight.//Worked out pretty hard this morning… Now I’m all fatigued.

Text.SourceString: Anything new going on?
Text.LocalizedString: Anything new going on?

Text.SourceString: I’m feeling tired today.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m feeling tired today.

Text.SourceString: One thing I’ve noticed about people here is they tend to like wildflowers.//<portrait=normal>Speaking of, though, I’ve heard not everybody likes violets…//So, watch out for that.
Text.LocalizedString: One thing I’ve noticed about people here is they tend to like wildflowers.//<portrait=normal>Speaking of, though, I’ve heard not everybody likes violets…//So, watch out for that.

Text.SourceString: I get it. Not a big violet fan myself.
Text.LocalizedString: I get it. Not a big violet fan myself.

Text.SourceString: You’re a farmer, right?//Let me ask you something. Is a passion fruit the same as a fig?
Text.LocalizedString: You’re a farmer, right?//Let me ask you something. Is a passion fruit the same as a fig?

Text.SourceString: I like this place, Coral Island.//It shows there’s more to life than climbing the corporate ladder.
Text.LocalizedString: I like this place, Coral Island.//It shows there’s more to life than climbing the corporate ladder.

Text.SourceString: Do you know how to make green smoothies?//Because <NpcName>Alice</> and <NpcName>Suki</> love them.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you know how to make green smoothies?//Because <NpcName>Alice</> and <NpcName>Suki</> love them.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, the twins. Wait, you knew they were twins?//<portrait=normal>I couldn’t believe it when I first found out.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, the twins. Wait, you knew they were twins?//<portrait=normal>I couldn’t believe it when I first found out.

Text.SourceString: I don’t miss the city as much as I thought I would.//<portrait=concerned>There’s not much there for me to miss.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t miss the city as much as I thought I would.//<portrait=concerned>There’s not much there for me to miss.

Text.SourceString: I find all kinds of things in the cavern.//<portrait=annoyed>Some of them are very…weird.
Text.LocalizedString: I find all kinds of things in the cavern.//<portrait=annoyed>Some of them are very…weird.

Text.SourceString: You get so tired after mining all day, yeah.//<portrait=sad>Wow… It's like a thrilling workout!
Text.LocalizedString: You get so tired after mining all day, yeah.//<portrait=sad>Wow… It's like a thrilling workout!

Text.SourceString: I meant me, not you. Mining tires me out.
Text.LocalizedString: I meant me, not you. Mining tires me out.

Text.SourceString: I’m ready to get back to work! Last weekend was wild.//The people here are so much fun.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m ready to get back to work! Last weekend was wild.//The people here are so much fun.

Text.SourceString: Your weekend was fun, I hope?
Text.LocalizedString: Your weekend was fun, I hope?

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Frank</> made us one of his experimental recipes last weekend.//<portrait=happy>Heh heh… Wowza! <PlayerName>$Player</>, you need to try it. Even just once.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Frank</> made us one of his experimental recipes last weekend.//<portrait=happy>Heh heh… Wowza! <PlayerName>$Player</>, you need to try it. Even just once.

Text.SourceString: Cross it off your bucket list!
Text.LocalizedString: Cross it off your bucket list!

Text.SourceString: You’re not allergic to moss or anything, right?//<portrait=normal>Because there’s lots of moss around the cavern.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re not allergic to moss or anything, right?//<portrait=normal>Because there’s lots of moss around the cavern.

Text.SourceString: I’d be careful going into the cavern, if I were you.//In case you slip and accidentally get a mouthful of moss.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d be careful going into the cavern, if I were you.//In case you slip and accidentally get a mouthful of moss.

Text.SourceString: On my second cup of tea today.//Now I'm all jittery. Caffeine powers activate!
Text.LocalizedString: On my second cup of tea today.//Now I'm all jittery. Caffeine powers activate!

Text.SourceString: I'm trying to cut back on coffee and get my caffeine fix from tea instead.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm trying to cut back on coffee and get my caffeine fix from tea instead.

Text.SourceString: Less jitters, more flavor, and all the charm.//<portrait=sad>Yeah, uh, I don't know why but coffee and I just don’t mix.
Text.LocalizedString: Less jitters, more flavor, and all the charm.//<portrait=sad>Yeah, uh, I don't know why but coffee and I just don’t mix.

Text.SourceString: When I’m cleaning artifacts, I try not to use too much chemical solution because I’m afraid it might damage them.
Text.LocalizedString: When I’m cleaning artifacts, I try not to use too much chemical solution because I’m afraid it might damage them.

Text.SourceString: But some is needed to break through the crust.//So there’s a careful balance we archeologists have to strike.
Text.LocalizedString: But some is needed to break through the crust.//So there’s a careful balance we archeologists have to strike.

Text.SourceString: I think I used too much hair gel today.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I used too much hair gel today.

Text.SourceString: Still looks good, though, so I’m not stressed about it.
Text.LocalizedString: Still looks good, though, so I’m not stressed about it.

Text.SourceString: The cavern in the forest is surprisingly deep.//There are all kinds of things buried down there.
Text.LocalizedString: The cavern in the forest is surprisingly deep.//There are all kinds of things buried down there.

Text.SourceString: If you’re lucky, you can even find weapons.//<portrait=concerned>Now, how they got there in the first place, nobody knows…
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re lucky, you can even find weapons.//<portrait=concerned>Now, how they got there in the first place, nobody knows…

Text.SourceString: I try to always have my bag with me.//<portrait=normal>How else am I going to be the dashing treasure hunter that I am?
Text.LocalizedString: I try to always have my bag with me.//<portrait=normal>How else am I going to be the dashing treasure hunter that I am?

Text.SourceString: With my bare hands? Ha! We're far more sophisticated than that, my dear.
Text.LocalizedString: With my bare hands? Ha! We're far more sophisticated than that, my dear.

Text.SourceString: Some of my friends meet up at the community center on Wednesday nights.//They share their feelings and support each other and stuff.//You can join them, if you want to.
Text.LocalizedString: Some of my friends meet up at the community center on Wednesday nights.//They share their feelings and support each other and stuff.//You can join them, if you want to.

Text.SourceString: Or is it Thursday nights? Hmm…//I don’t remember.
Text.LocalizedString: Or is it Thursday nights? Hmm…//I don’t remember.

Text.SourceString: I’m not a weapon kind of guy, so I stick to mining on level 2.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not a weapon kind of guy, so I stick to mining on level 2.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been practicing with a saber, but it isn’t a one-and-done type of situation, you know?//One day, when I've mastered it, I'll venture even deeper into the cavern...and into your heart.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been practicing with a saber, but it isn’t a one-and-done type of situation, you know?//One day, when I've mastered it, I'll venture even deeper into the cavern...and into your heart.

Text.SourceString: Just so you know, <PlayerName>$Player</>, my work doesn't end at the museum.//I have my own digging expeditions on Thursdays.
Text.LocalizedString: Just so you know, <PlayerName>$Player</>, my work doesn't end at the museum.//I have my own digging expeditions on Thursdays.

Text.SourceString: Ugh, but I draw the line at digging in Summer.//<portrait=annoyed>The cavern turns into a sauna, and this adventurer can't handle the heat.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh, but I draw the line at digging in Summer.//<portrait=annoyed>The cavern turns into a sauna, and this adventurer can't handle the heat.

Text.SourceString: I made the best falafel the other day.//I’m so proud of myself.
Text.LocalizedString: I made the best falafel the other day.//I’m so proud of myself.

Text.SourceString: What a farm you’ve got!
Text.LocalizedString: What a farm you’ve got!

Text.SourceString: I cut through your farm on my way to the cavern and saw how much work you’ve put in. I have newfound respect for you.
Text.LocalizedString: I cut through your farm on my way to the cavern and saw how much work you’ve put in. I have newfound respect for you.

Text.SourceString: I like working in the field as much as I do in the museum. I’m glad I decided to move here. There are a lot of places to dig.
Text.LocalizedString: I like working in the field as much as I do in the museum. I’m glad I decided to move here. There are a lot of places to dig.

Text.SourceString: I tried dating before. Three serious relationships, in fact. I guess I’m not that good at it, because they all crashed and burned.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried dating before. Three serious relationships, in fact. I guess I’m not that good at it, because they all crashed and burned.

Text.SourceString: For a second there, I thought I might be the problem.//<portrait=happy>But, nah! Can’t be. *laughs* All right, that’s enough psychotherapy for one day.
Text.LocalizedString: For a second there, I thought I might be the problem.//<portrait=happy>But, nah! Can’t be. *laughs* All right, that’s enough psychotherapy for one day.

Text.SourceString: I’m trying to read this book <NpcName>Millie</> told me about. <Italic>The Fairy Tales of Dulca</> or something like that.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m trying to read this book <NpcName>Millie</> told me about. <Italic>The Fairy Tales of Dulca</> or something like that.

Text.SourceString: I can’t seem to get past the third chapter. You haven’t read it, have you?//I just need to know the gist of it.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t seem to get past the third chapter. You haven’t read it, have you?//I just need to know the gist of it.

Text.SourceString: Technically, I’m working today. I’m just not in the office.
Text.LocalizedString: Technically, I’m working today. I’m just not in the office.

Text.SourceString: I'm more of a roguish, on-the-go kind of worker today, you know what I mean?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm more of a roguish, on-the-go kind of worker today, you know what I mean?

Text.SourceString: I had this mind-blowing epiphany recently... I realized how little I actually know about this island.
Text.LocalizedString: I had this mind-blowing epiphany recently... I realized how little I actually know about this island.

Text.SourceString: I keep stumbling upon these mind-boggling artifacts. Like, seriously, I once found a gigantic spoon at sea.
Text.LocalizedString: I keep stumbling upon these mind-boggling artifacts. Like, seriously, I once found a gigantic spoon at sea.

Text.SourceString: I'm talking a spoon as big as my head! What on earth is going on?//<portrait=normal>Are there giant mermaids with massive cutlery roaming around?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm talking a spoon as big as my head! What on earth is going on?//<portrait=normal>Are there giant mermaids with massive cutlery roaming around?

Text.SourceString: I like <NpcName>Charles</>, but he can be a bit uptight.//Sure, I leave the fridge door open every once in a while, and I’ve accidentally eaten his food, but…
Text.LocalizedString: I like <NpcName>Charles</>, but he can be a bit uptight.//Sure, I leave the fridge door open every once in a while, and I’ve accidentally eaten his food, but…

Text.SourceString: Um… It sounds worse when I say it out loud. Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: Um… It sounds worse when I say it out loud. Hmm…

Text.SourceString: I need to stop bringing work home with me. It has caused one too many incidents.//This one time, I was cleaning up my geodes in the kitchen. Some dirt must have fallen from them, and it ended up in <NpcName>Charles’s</> burrito…
Text.LocalizedString: I need to stop bringing work home with me. It has caused one too many incidents.//This one time, I was cleaning up my geodes in the kitchen. Some dirt must have fallen from them, and it ended up in <NpcName>Charles’s</> burrito…

Text.SourceString: Man, was he mad at me!//Apparently he bit into gravel and almost lost a tooth. I actually felt awful.
Text.LocalizedString: Man, was he mad at me!//Apparently he bit into gravel and almost lost a tooth. I actually felt awful.

Text.SourceString: Personally, I’m not big on cut flowers. I prefer to enjoy them growing outside.//But what flowers do you like, <PlayerName>$Player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Personally, I’m not big on cut flowers. I prefer to enjoy them growing outside.//But what flowers do you like, <PlayerName>$Player</>?

Text.SourceString: You like tulips? I don’t, personally. I don’t know… They just don’t do it for me.
Text.LocalizedString: You like tulips? I don’t, personally. I don’t know… They just don’t do it for me.

Text.SourceString: They are pretty, aren’t they? But I can’t have flowers at home. <NpcName>Charles</> won’t stop sneezing if I do.
Text.LocalizedString: They are pretty, aren’t they? But I can’t have flowers at home. <NpcName>Charles</> won’t stop sneezing if I do.

Special.SourceString: Not a fan of flowers. I’ve tried several… They didn’t taste very good.
Special.LocalizedString: Not a fan of flowers. I’ve tried several… They didn’t taste very good.

Text.SourceString: Another Spring…another year begins…another birthday season for me.//Yep, my birthday’s on the 12th. Two days after the Cherry Blossom Festival.
Text.LocalizedString: Another Spring…another year begins…another birthday season for me.//Yep, my birthday’s on the 12th. Two days after the Cherry Blossom Festival.

Text.SourceString: I’m getting back into my routine now… I can get to the cavern more easily.//The path to the forest isn’t so slippery now the snow’s melted.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m getting back into my routine now… I can get to the cavern more easily.//The path to the forest isn’t so slippery now the snow’s melted.

Text.SourceString: I see more and more people outdoors now the weather is <Italic>livable</> again…
Text.LocalizedString: I see more and more people outdoors now the weather is <Italic>livable</> again…

Text.SourceString: One of my worst heartbreaks happened in Spring… It was in the second grade.//We were in the same class. She rejected the worm I found outside and went to play on the monkey bars with Aiden… I wonder how that guy’s doing now…
Text.LocalizedString: One of my worst heartbreaks happened in Spring… It was in the second grade.//We were in the same class. She rejected the worm I found outside and went to play on the monkey bars with Aiden… I wonder how that guy’s doing now…

Text.SourceString: I did a new workout regimen for Winter.//It was a fifteen-day thing. Can you tell? I'm all about those toned muscles now, baby.
Text.LocalizedString: I did a new workout regimen for Winter.//It was a fifteen-day thing. Can you tell? I'm all about those toned muscles now, baby.

Text.SourceString: I like having breakfast outdoors while looking at the flowers.//Something about it… Especially Spring flowers.
Text.LocalizedString: I like having breakfast outdoors while looking at the flowers.//Something about it… Especially Spring flowers.

Text.SourceString: If you’re okay with humidity, you should visit the cavern in Summer.//It’s usually pretty cool inside.
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re okay with humidity, you should visit the cavern in Summer.//It’s usually pretty cool inside.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know if it’s the Summer heat, or… I don’t know what, but one of the shafts in the cavern is so hot lately.//Weird thing is it’s just that one, though… Like something is flaming inside.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know if it’s the Summer heat, or… I don’t know what, but one of the shafts in the cavern is so hot lately.//Weird thing is it’s just that one, though… Like something is flaming inside.

Text.SourceString: My cavern-o-meter isn’t a fancy one, but it picked up the different temperatures in the shafts.//It’s weird. You see, temperatures down there don’t usually change like that.//Even in Summer!
Text.LocalizedString: My cavern-o-meter isn’t a fancy one, but it picked up the different temperatures in the shafts.//It’s weird. You see, temperatures down there don’t usually change like that.//Even in Summer!

Text.SourceString: Better soak up the last of that Summer sun, <PlayerName>$Player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Better soak up the last of that Summer sun, <PlayerName>$Player</>.

Text.SourceString: I’m ready to soak up the sun!//<portrait=annoyed>And if you’re going to remind me about sunscreen, don’t worry. I get an earful every day from <NPCName>Charles</>.//Sunscreen, sunscreen, sunscreen…
Text.LocalizedString: I’m ready to soak up the sun!//<portrait=annoyed>And if you’re going to remind me about sunscreen, don’t worry. I get an earful every day from <NPCName>Charles</>.//Sunscreen, sunscreen, sunscreen…

Text.SourceString: Thinking of playing volleyball at the beach tomorrow. Wonder if anyone will be up for a match.//<portrait=concerned><NPCName>Chaem</> maybe? Or…//<portrait=normal>Will you be there?
Text.LocalizedString: Thinking of playing volleyball at the beach tomorrow. Wonder if anyone will be up for a match.//<portrait=concerned><NPCName>Chaem</> maybe? Or…//<portrait=normal>Will you be there?

Text.SourceString: I don’t mind the walk to the forest, especially on nice Summer days.//I get to see what <NPCName>Dinda’s</> planting, see what <NPCName>Joko’s</> up to. All that stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mind the walk to the forest, especially on nice Summer days.//I get to see what <NPCName>Dinda’s</> planting, see what <NPCName>Joko’s</> up to. All that stuff.

Text.SourceString: Don’t you think jazz is the perfect background music for Fall?//Love jazz. It's smooth, it's classy, it's everything you need to embrace the cozy vibes.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t you think jazz is the perfect background music for Fall?//Love jazz. It's smooth, it's classy, it's everything you need to embrace the cozy vibes.

Text.SourceString: The ground in Fall feels a bit different from other seasons. That’s the first thing I notice, usually.//That and the leaves changing color.
Text.LocalizedString: The ground in Fall feels a bit different from other seasons. That’s the first thing I notice, usually.//That and the leaves changing color.

Text.SourceString: There are so many mushrooms in the forest now.//I don’t do that kind of thing, but if you like them, you should go forage around.
Text.LocalizedString: There are so many mushrooms in the forest now.//I don’t do that kind of thing, but if you like them, you should go forage around.

Text.SourceString: *singing* Mmm shoopadoo wawa hmmmm~
Text.LocalizedString: *singing* Mmm shoopadoo wawa hmmmm~

Text.SourceString: Oh, sorry, <PlayerName>$Player</>. I just had this jazz melody in my head.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, sorry, <PlayerName>$Player</>. I just had this jazz melody in my head.

Text.SourceString: I live by the water. It’s nice and cool in the morning.
Text.LocalizedString: I live by the water. It’s nice and cool in the morning.

Text.SourceString: The air in the cavern is much warmer than outside, especially with the snow everywhere.//Rocks are great insulators. Caverns stay relatively the same temperature year round.
Text.LocalizedString: The air in the cavern is much warmer than outside, especially with the snow everywhere.//Rocks are great insulators. Caverns stay relatively the same temperature year round.

Text.SourceString: Cool when it’s Summer, warm in Winter… That sort of thing.
Text.LocalizedString: Cool when it’s Summer, warm in Winter… That sort of thing.

Text.SourceString: Remember to be extra careful walking to the forest. Icy path and all.
Text.LocalizedString: Remember to be extra careful walking to the forest. Icy path and all.

Text.SourceString: It’s Winter again. Time does fly when you’re having fun!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s Winter again. Time does fly when you’re having fun!

Text.SourceString: Lots of animals hibernate in Winter… Ever wonder which ones hibernate in the caverns?
Text.LocalizedString: Lots of animals hibernate in Winter… Ever wonder which ones hibernate in the caverns?

Text.SourceString: Having breakfast outdoors is different in Winter… Do not recommend it.
Text.LocalizedString: Having breakfast outdoors is different in Winter… Do not recommend it.

Text.SourceString: The mayor came by the library the other day and told us a drilling corporation is moving into town.
Text.LocalizedString: The mayor came by the library the other day and told us a drilling corporation is moving into town.

Text.SourceString: The Catfish Corp, I think?
Text.LocalizedString: The Catfish Corp, I think?

Text.SourceString: Oh, yeah! Pufferfish Corp! There you go.//<portrait=annoyed>Fitting name, don’t you think?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, yeah! Pufferfish Corp! There you go.//<portrait=annoyed>Fitting name, don’t you think?

Text.SourceString: Phew! That New Year’s Eve dinner was unreal!//<portrait=happy>So many fruit pies to choose from.
Text.LocalizedString: Phew! That New Year’s Eve dinner was unreal!//<portrait=happy>So many fruit pies to choose from.

Text.SourceString: Have you started working on your farm yet?//There must be a lot of weeding to do.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you started working on your farm yet?//There must be a lot of weeding to do.

Text.SourceString: I’m so sore. I’ve been lifting a lot lately.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so sore. I’ve been lifting a lot lately.

Text.SourceString: Can you tell?
Text.LocalizedString: Can you tell?

Text.SourceString: My Summer didn’t start out great, but thanks for asking.//<portrait=normal>How’s your Summer so far?
Text.LocalizedString: My Summer didn’t start out great, but thanks for asking.//<portrait=normal>How’s your Summer so far?

Text.SourceString: I woke up yesterday with bug bites on my ankles.//<portrait=angry>My ankles, <PlayerName>$Player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: I woke up yesterday with bug bites on my ankles.//<portrait=angry>My ankles, <PlayerName>$Player</>!

Text.SourceString: I grew up fishing with my dad. We would wake up early on the weekend, around 4 am, and catch a boat to go fishing at sea.
Text.LocalizedString: I grew up fishing with my dad. We would wake up early on the weekend, around 4 am, and catch a boat to go fishing at sea.

Text.SourceString: We’d bring our lunches out and sail home at sunset. Then Dad and I would stop by a ramen place on the way home for dinner. We’d cook up our catch the next day.
Text.LocalizedString: We’d bring our lunches out and sail home at sunset. Then Dad and I would stop by a ramen place on the way home for dinner. We’d cook up our catch the next day.

Text.SourceString: I feel sticky… Yuck.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel sticky… Yuck.

Text.SourceString: Oh, I’m not too worried about mosquitoes. They prefer one particular blood type over the other.//And mine happens to be “the other.”
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, I’m not too worried about mosquitoes. They prefer one particular blood type over the other.//And mine happens to be “the other.”

Text.SourceString: The cavern is wild, though. The mosquitos attack no matter what… Maybe because there are no other targets down there.
Text.LocalizedString: The cavern is wild, though. The mosquitos attack no matter what… Maybe because there are no other targets down there.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know how long my hair can survive in this heat.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know how long my hair can survive in this heat.

Text.SourceString: I have these holes in my shoes that keep my feet nice and cool.
Text.LocalizedString: I have these holes in my shoes that keep my feet nice and cool.

Text.SourceString: Have you got those holes in your shoes?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you got those holes in your shoes?

Text.SourceString: Do you know this song? For some reason it’s been stuck in my head. It goes…
Text.LocalizedString: Do you know this song? For some reason it’s been stuck in my head. It goes…

Text.SourceString: *singing* Dooo doo doo dooo doo dooooo…
Text.LocalizedString: *singing* Dooo doo doo dooo doo dooooo…

Text.SourceString: Did you catch the melody, <PlayerName>$Player</>? I forget what it’s called.
Text.LocalizedString: Did you catch the melody, <PlayerName>$Player</>? I forget what it’s called.

Text.SourceString: Not many plants can survive the Winter snow. I hope it means less work for you.
Text.LocalizedString: Not many plants can survive the Winter snow. I hope it means less work for you.

Text.SourceString: Maybe you can bring us some more of those artifacts from the cavern.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe you can bring us some more of those artifacts from the cavern.

Text.SourceString: In less than three weeks, it’ll be the New Year. I’m psyched!
Text.LocalizedString: In less than three weeks, it’ll be the New Year. I’m psyched!

Text.SourceString: I need to make sure to stock up on tea.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to make sure to stock up on tea.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… I’m going straight home after work.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… I’m going straight home after work.

Text.SourceString: I guess I’ll just heat up yesterday’s leftover tacos for dinner.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess I’ll just heat up yesterday’s leftover tacos for dinner.

Text.SourceString: I hope they’re still good. Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: I hope they’re still good. Hmm…

Text.SourceString: When it isn’t raining, I like to spend my weekends drinking coffee in front of the house.//You know, doing some people watching.
Text.LocalizedString: When it isn’t raining, I like to spend my weekends drinking coffee in front of the house.//You know, doing some people watching.

Text.SourceString: I figure I’ll stay inside today.//I’m trying not to get too much mud in the house.
Text.LocalizedString: I figure I’ll stay inside today.//I’m trying not to get too much mud in the house.

Text.SourceString: The thunder woke me up at two o’clock this morning!
Text.LocalizedString: The thunder woke me up at two o’clock this morning!

Text.SourceString: I couldn’t go back to bed after that.
Text.LocalizedString: I couldn’t go back to bed after that.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… I’m going straight home after work.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… I’m going straight home after work.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… I’m going straight home after work.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… I’m going straight home after work.

Text.SourceString: Another year has passed.
Text.LocalizedString: Another year has passed.

Text.SourceString: There are things I wish I’d handled differently.
Text.LocalizedString: There are things I wish I’d handled differently.

Text.SourceString: Friends are important to me.//So I try my best to set aside some time every week to keep up with them.
Text.LocalizedString: Friends are important to me.//So I try my best to set aside some time every week to keep up with them.

Text.SourceString: Working on these artifacts may sound odd, but it's actually incredible. Listen up...//It's like having a time-travel portal right here, allowing us a glimpse into the fascinating world of our ancestors.//The artifacts take me back in time.
Text.LocalizedString: Working on these artifacts may sound odd, but it's actually incredible. Listen up...//It's like having a time-travel portal right here, allowing us a glimpse into the fascinating world of our ancestors.//The artifacts take me back in time.

Text.SourceString: A glimpse of what life was like… A quick look at how the world was hundreds of years ago.
Text.LocalizedString: A glimpse of what life was like… A quick look at how the world was hundreds of years ago.

Text.SourceString: Some of the artifacts here are ones I found.//My little contribution to the field I'm so passionate about.
Text.LocalizedString: Some of the artifacts here are ones I found.//My little contribution to the field I'm so passionate about.

Text.SourceString: Call it being part of history, yeah? Making my mark.
Text.LocalizedString: Call it being part of history, yeah? Making my mark.

Text.SourceString: If you think about it, these artifacts and fossils right here are like silent witnesses.//They’ve seen things, <PlayerName>$Player</>, that you and I have never even thought about.
Text.LocalizedString: If you think about it, these artifacts and fossils right here are like silent witnesses.//They’ve seen things, <PlayerName>$Player</>, that you and I have never even thought about.

Text.SourceString: And these artifacts know things you and I will never figure out.
Text.LocalizedString: And these artifacts know things you and I will never figure out.

Text.SourceString: Well, of course I know some of it… But yeah.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, of course I know some of it… But yeah.

Text.SourceString: *mumbling to himself* Is it <NpcName>Frank</> or Rank?//Oh well, let's just roll with it.
Text.LocalizedString: *mumbling to himself* Is it <NpcName>Frank</> or Rank?//Oh well, let's just roll with it.

Text.SourceString: You freaked me out. Say hi next time, will you?
Text.LocalizedString: You freaked me out. Say hi next time, will you?

Text.SourceString: I’m so sore… I’ve been lifting a lot lately.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so sore… I’ve been lifting a lot lately.

Text.SourceString: A nice hot bath sounds excellent right about now.
Text.LocalizedString: A nice hot bath sounds excellent right about now.

Text.SourceString: I had a full day today… I think I deserve to unwind a bit before heading home.
Text.LocalizedString: I had a full day today… I think I deserve to unwind a bit before heading home.

Text.SourceString: One more over here, <NpcName>Frank</>!
Text.LocalizedString: One more over here, <NpcName>Frank</>!

Text.SourceString: What a great way to end the day.
Text.LocalizedString: What a great way to end the day.

Text.SourceString: Do you come here often? I do.//The food’s good, and it’s close to the house and my work.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you come here often? I do.//The food’s good, and it’s close to the house and my work.

Text.SourceString: Besides, listening to <NpcName>Frank</> is better than TV.
Text.LocalizedString: Besides, listening to <NpcName>Frank</> is better than TV.

Text.SourceString: Hey, <NpcName>Frank</>! I want to make sure you heard what I just said!
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, <NpcName>Frank</>! I want to make sure you heard what I just said!

Text.SourceString: Growing old? Nah, doesn't stress me out. But hey, I gotta admit, I do have a tiny worry.//<portrait=sad>What if I have to do this whole "growing old" thing alone? Now that's a scary thought.
Text.LocalizedString: Growing old? Nah, doesn't stress me out. But hey, I gotta admit, I do have a tiny worry.//<portrait=sad>What if I have to do this whole "growing old" thing alone? Now that's a scary thought.

Text.SourceString: I know I complain about <NpcName>Charles</> sometimes, but deep down, I know I'll miss that dude if he decides to move on.
Text.LocalizedString: I know I complain about <NpcName>Charles</> sometimes, but deep down, I know I'll miss that dude if he decides to move on.

Text.SourceString: I’m brushing up on my fishing.//Just a little hobby I like to do in my spare time.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m brushing up on my fishing.//Just a little hobby I like to do in my spare time.

Text.SourceString: I just don’t have time to make my own bait.//<portrait=concerned>Besides, <NpcName>Charles</> gets cranky when I start making a mess at the house.
Text.LocalizedString: I just don’t have time to make my own bait.//<portrait=concerned>Besides, <NpcName>Charles</> gets cranky when I start making a mess at the house.

Text.SourceString: Are you out to go fishing too, <PlayerName>$Player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you out to go fishing too, <PlayerName>$Player</>?

Text.SourceString: One time, I caught myself a couple of pink snappers within ten minutes of each other.//I’m still amazed about it to this day.
Text.LocalizedString: One time, I caught myself a couple of pink snappers within ten minutes of each other.//I’m still amazed about it to this day.

Text.SourceString: Fingers crossed, <PlayerName>$Player</>. It might happen again!
Text.LocalizedString: Fingers crossed, <PlayerName>$Player</>. It might happen again!

Text.SourceString: Growing up, Dad would wake me up early on the weekend to go fishing at sea… At around 4 am.
Text.LocalizedString: Growing up, Dad would wake me up early on the weekend to go fishing at sea… At around 4 am.

Text.SourceString: We would bring our lunches out and sail home at sunset.//Then Dad and I would stop by a ramen place on the way home for dinner.//We’d cook up our catch the next day.
Text.LocalizedString: We would bring our lunches out and sail home at sunset.//Then Dad and I would stop by a ramen place on the way home for dinner.//We’d cook up our catch the next day.

Text.SourceString: I smell like the ocean.
Text.LocalizedString: I smell like the ocean.

Text.SourceString: A hint of saltiness that's hard to resist.//Care for a taste?
Text.LocalizedString: A hint of saltiness that's hard to resist.//Care for a taste?

Text.SourceString: Did you bring vitamins with you?
Text.LocalizedString: Did you bring vitamins with you?

Text.SourceString: I’m not a weapon kind of guy, so I limit my mining to level 2.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not a weapon kind of guy, so I limit my mining to level 2.

Text.SourceString: But I still wear armor, you know… Just in case.
Text.LocalizedString: But I still wear armor, you know… Just in case.

Text.SourceString: I think I’ll go out for a bit and have a snack by the creek.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ll go out for a bit and have a snack by the creek.

Text.SourceString: Whoa!
Text.LocalizedString: Whoa!

Text.SourceString: I didn’t hear you. This cavern can get a bit creepy.
Text.LocalizedString: I didn’t hear you. This cavern can get a bit creepy.

Text.SourceString: Ah, I didn’t get anything valuable today.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, I didn’t get anything valuable today.

Text.SourceString: But at least I got a good workout in the cavern.
Text.LocalizedString: But at least I got a good workout in the cavern.

Text.SourceString: This is a nice spot for a lunch break.//I might cool my feet in the creek afterward.
Text.LocalizedString: This is a nice spot for a lunch break.//I might cool my feet in the creek afterward.

Text.SourceString: Yikes! Something came at me in the dark, so I ran as fast as I could.
Text.LocalizedString: Yikes! Something came at me in the dark, so I ran as fast as I could.

Text.SourceString: I’m still trying to catch my breath, uh, yeah...
Text.LocalizedString: I’m still trying to catch my breath, uh, yeah...

Text.SourceString: Did you hear what happened at the Tavern last week?//<portrait=normal>It was wild. <NPCName>Pablo</> did a cartwheel off the counter, and everyone cheered.
Text.LocalizedString: Did you hear what happened at the Tavern last week?//<portrait=normal>It was wild. <NPCName>Pablo</> did a cartwheel off the counter, and everyone cheered.

Text.SourceString: You gotta come hang out with us one night.//It’ll be the time of your life, I promise!
Text.LocalizedString: You gotta come hang out with us one night.//It’ll be the time of your life, I promise!

Text.SourceString: I’m pretty sure no one’s beaten my mini golf score yet.//<portrait=happy>Think you’re up for the challenge?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m pretty sure no one’s beaten my mini golf score yet.//<portrait=happy>Think you’re up for the challenge?

Text.SourceString: What’s your favorite thing to eat around here?//<portrait=concerned>I’m starving.
Text.LocalizedString: What’s your favorite thing to eat around here?//<portrait=concerned>I’m starving.

Text.SourceString: I know there’s tons of fresh veggies and stuff, but sometimes you just really want fast food, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: I know there’s tons of fresh veggies and stuff, but sometimes you just really want fast food, you know?

Text.SourceString: There’s so much cool stuff in the cavern, but no one likes to get their hands dirty down there.//It’s too bad.//<portrait=happy>More for me, I guess!
Text.LocalizedString: There’s so much cool stuff in the cavern, but no one likes to get their hands dirty down there.//It’s too bad.//<portrait=happy>More for me, I guess!

Text.SourceString: Do you think the town would let me start a cornhole festival?//<portrait=happy>Probably not. I’d win every year.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think the town would let me start a cornhole festival?//<portrait=happy>Probably not. I’d win every year.

Text.SourceString: I should start a Coral Island singles club.//Living in the same house, throwing epic parties, and inviting other singles to join in the fun... Sounds like a recipe for unforgettable memories.//<portrait=happy>And who knows, maybe some connections will be made along the way.
Text.LocalizedString: I should start a Coral Island singles club.//Living in the same house, throwing epic parties, and inviting other singles to join in the fun... Sounds like a recipe for unforgettable memories.//<portrait=happy>And who knows, maybe some connections will be made along the way.

Text.SourceString: I did that in college, and it was awesome.//<portrait=normal>Gah, I miss those days.
Text.LocalizedString: I did that in college, and it was awesome.//<portrait=normal>Gah, I miss those days.

Text.SourceString: Between working in the cavern and hanging out, I hardly get any time to myself these days.
Text.LocalizedString: Between working in the cavern and hanging out, I hardly get any time to myself these days.

Text.SourceString: They should play more jazz at the Tavern.//<portrait=happy>It would give it that classy, ritzy feel. Know what I mean?
Text.LocalizedString: They should play more jazz at the Tavern.//<portrait=happy>It would give it that classy, ritzy feel. Know what I mean?

Text.SourceString: Picture us...you and me...sipping cocktails, swaying to the smooth tunes... Now that's my kind of evening.
Text.LocalizedString: Picture us...you and me...sipping cocktails, swaying to the smooth tunes... Now that's my kind of evening.

Text.SourceString: I kinda feel bad for <NPCName>Suki</>.//<portrait=concerned>She seems to be doing well with her ex, but she still had to go through a divorce.
Text.LocalizedString: I kinda feel bad for <NPCName>Suki</>.//<portrait=concerned>She seems to be doing well with her ex, but she still had to go through a divorce.

Text.SourceString: Can’t get divorced if you don’t get married! That’s my philosophy.
Text.LocalizedString: Can’t get divorced if you don’t get married! That’s my philosophy.

Text.SourceString: I’ve seen people around here pull in some pretty big fish from the ocean.//<portrait=concerned> Makes me wonder what else you could find down there.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve seen people around here pull in some pretty big fish from the ocean.//<portrait=concerned> Makes me wonder what else you could find down there.

Text.SourceString: Note to self: Be stealthy when coming home tonight.//<portrait=annoyed>Last week <NPCName>Charles</> got mad. Apparently I was “too loud” coming in.
Text.LocalizedString: Note to self: Be stealthy when coming home tonight.//<portrait=annoyed>Last week <NPCName>Charles</> got mad. Apparently I was “too loud” coming in.

Text.SourceString: It’s not my fault <NPCName>Charles</> was in bed at 11 pm on a Friday.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s not my fault <NPCName>Charles</> was in bed at 11 pm on a Friday.

Text.SourceString: There’s nothing better than okra and turnips. They remind me of my mom’s cooking.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s nothing better than okra and turnips. They remind me of my mom’s cooking.

Text.SourceString: Mom always made sure the fridge was stocked with food and snacks and whatever.//<portrait=happy>What a champ!
Text.LocalizedString: Mom always made sure the fridge was stocked with food and snacks and whatever.//<portrait=happy>What a champ!

Text.SourceString: I heard some people at the Tavern say they like swimming in the ocean, which is awesome! Lots to see down there, I’m sure.//<portrait=happy>Me? I’m more of a forest guy myself.
Text.LocalizedString: I heard some people at the Tavern say they like swimming in the ocean, which is awesome! Lots to see down there, I’m sure.//<portrait=happy>Me? I’m more of a forest guy myself.

Text.SourceString: They need some new drink recipes down at the Tavern.//<portrait=concerned>I wonder if there’s anything they could make with turnips and okra.
Text.LocalizedString: They need some new drink recipes down at the Tavern.//<portrait=concerned>I wonder if there’s anything they could make with turnips and okra.

Text.SourceString: I’d call it the Scott Seltzer!//<portrait=normal>That has a nice ring to it, right?
Text.LocalizedString: I’d call it the Scott Seltzer!//<portrait=normal>That has a nice ring to it, right?

Text.SourceString: I went to this one party in college where everything was decorated in gold.//<portrait=annoyed>Not just a gold color, but actual, legit gold.
Text.LocalizedString: I went to this one party in college where everything was decorated in gold.//<portrait=annoyed>Not just a gold color, but actual, legit gold.

Text.SourceString: It was cool. Definitely one of those once-in-a-lifetime experiences.
Text.LocalizedString: It was cool. Definitely one of those once-in-a-lifetime experiences.

Text.SourceString: I’ve tried to get <NPCName>Charles</> a date, but I struck out.//He just wants to sit at the bar and give unsolicited medical advice…//<portrait=annoyed>He’s never going to find a partner like that.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve tried to get <NPCName>Charles</> a date, but I struck out.//He just wants to sit at the bar and give unsolicited medical advice…//<portrait=annoyed>He’s never going to find a partner like that.

Text.SourceString: I don’t really miss the city.//The sunsets here are much nicer… In the city, all the buildings block your view of the sky.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t really miss the city.//The sunsets here are much nicer… In the city, all the buildings block your view of the sky.

Text.SourceString: Have you seen the stuff <NPCName>Ben</> has in his caravan?//He finds some neat things sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you seen the stuff <NPCName>Ben</> has in his caravan?//He finds some neat things sometimes.

Text.SourceString: He found a gold necklace once and put it on his duck.//<portrait=happy>What a guy!
Text.LocalizedString: He found a gold necklace once and put it on his duck.//<portrait=happy>What a guy!

Text.SourceString: Since you’re here, let me ask you a question.//<portrait=concerned>What’s the best way to fold a shirt?
Text.LocalizedString: Since you’re here, let me ask you a question.//<portrait=concerned>What’s the best way to fold a shirt?

Text.SourceString: I remember my mom telling me once, but I totally wasn’t paying attention.//Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: I remember my mom telling me once, but I totally wasn’t paying attention.//Hmm…

Text.SourceString: I’ve been seeing a lot of you recently. You sure do get around, don’t you?//<portrait=happy>It’s kind of nice.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been seeing a lot of you recently. You sure do get around, don’t you?//<portrait=happy>It’s kind of nice.

Text.SourceString: Find me next time you’re at the Tavern, and I’ll have <NPCName>Frank</> fix you up something special.//<portrait=happy>Or better yet, I can fix it up!
Text.LocalizedString: Find me next time you’re at the Tavern, and I’ll have <NPCName>Frank</> fix you up something special.//<portrait=happy>Or better yet, I can fix it up!

Text.SourceString: The Spring rains erode the cavern a little more each year. Over time, more artifacts and gems are uncovered.//<portrait=happy>Don’t quote me on that, though. That’s just my theory!
Text.LocalizedString: The Spring rains erode the cavern a little more each year. Over time, more artifacts and gems are uncovered.//<portrait=happy>Don’t quote me on that, though. That’s just my theory!

Text.SourceString: There are bad things about rain too, if you think about it.//<portrait=annoyed>For one, if you don’t get to the artifacts in time, the rain can give them a beating. Heck, even destroy them!//<portrait=happy>That’s also my theory.
Text.LocalizedString: There are bad things about rain too, if you think about it.//<portrait=annoyed>For one, if you don’t get to the artifacts in time, the rain can give them a beating. Heck, even destroy them!//<portrait=happy>That’s also my theory.

Text.SourceString: Are you growing anything new this year, <PlayerName>$Player</>?//A big turnip and okra salad sounds delicious right about now.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you growing anything new this year, <PlayerName>$Player</>?//A big turnip and okra salad sounds delicious right about now.

Text.SourceString: They say the biggest fish come out in Summer.//You wanna see if I can catch any monsters down at the pier?
Text.LocalizedString: They say the biggest fish come out in Summer.//You wanna see if I can catch any monsters down at the pier?

Text.SourceString: The one thing Coral Island has over the city is beach life.//There’s nothing like blasting a cannonball right into the waves.
Text.LocalizedString: The one thing Coral Island has over the city is beach life.//There’s nothing like blasting a cannonball right into the waves.

Text.SourceString: I can’t believe it’s already Summer.//Sure feels like Winter was just a couple of days ago.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t believe it’s already Summer.//Sure feels like Winter was just a couple of days ago.

Text.SourceString: I love Summer! The sun is shining, the weather is warm, and there’s nothing better than hanging out at the beach.
Text.LocalizedString: I love Summer! The sun is shining, the weather is warm, and there’s nothing better than hanging out at the beach.

Text.SourceString: I could go on and on about how much I love Summer, but I think you get the idea.//<portrait=normal>It’s just the best season. Swimsuit every day!
Text.LocalizedString: I could go on and on about how much I love Summer, but I think you get the idea.//<portrait=normal>It’s just the best season. Swimsuit every day!

Text.SourceString: Fall is the time of year when people get into relationships, right?//So they can meet each other’s families during the holidays.
Text.LocalizedString: Fall is the time of year when people get into relationships, right?//So they can meet each other’s families during the holidays.

Text.SourceString: I used to date this girl who loved Fall.//She liked to jump in big piles of leaves and carve pumpkins.
Text.LocalizedString: I used to date this girl who loved Fall.//She liked to jump in big piles of leaves and carve pumpkins.

Text.SourceString: I wonder if there are big leaf piles where she is now.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if there are big leaf piles where she is now.

Text.SourceString: Am I ready for Winter?//<portrait=normal>Hmm… I guess so.
Text.LocalizedString: Am I ready for Winter?//<portrait=normal>Hmm… I guess so.

Text.SourceString: Fall is the perfect time of year for some good jazz.//<portrait=blushing>Don’t the falling leaves and the crisp breeze make you think of saxophones and trombones?
Text.LocalizedString: Fall is the perfect time of year for some good jazz.//<portrait=blushing>Don’t the falling leaves and the crisp breeze make you think of saxophones and trombones?

Text.SourceString: I need to tell <NPCName>Charles</> to turn the heat up in the house.//It’s really starting to get cold out here.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to tell <NPCName>Charles</> to turn the heat up in the house.//It’s really starting to get cold out here.

Text.SourceString: Is it just me, or does Winter seem like the quietest season?//<portrait=normal>Someone needs to turn up the volume out here.
Text.LocalizedString: Is it just me, or does Winter seem like the quietest season?//<portrait=normal>Someone needs to turn up the volume out here.

Text.SourceString: Winter just seems so depressing to me. It’s dark and cold, and everything is dead.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter just seems so depressing to me. It’s dark and cold, and everything is dead.

Text.SourceString: I heard <NPCName>Kenny</> say at the ranch that you gotta keep your animals inside during Winter.//Is it true?
Text.LocalizedString: I heard <NPCName>Kenny</> say at the ranch that you gotta keep your animals inside during Winter.//Is it true?

Text.SourceString: I guess you don’t want your milk and eggs to come out frozen.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess you don’t want your milk and eggs to come out frozen.

Text.SourceString: Give me sunshine and a swimsuit any day over snow and a parka.
Text.LocalizedString: Give me sunshine and a swimsuit any day over snow and a parka.

Text.SourceString: I think I’ll actually have to wear long pants when I go digging now.//The cavern’s all right this time of year, but it’s freezing on the walk over there.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ll actually have to wear long pants when I go digging now.//The cavern’s all right this time of year, but it’s freezing on the walk over there.

Text.SourceString: Everyone on the island seems to like Winter the most, but I’m really more of a Summer guy.//<portrait=happy>What’s not to love about sweating it out on the beach?
Text.LocalizedString: Everyone on the island seems to like Winter the most, but I’m really more of a Summer guy.//<portrait=happy>What’s not to love about sweating it out on the beach?

Text.SourceString: Coral Island has more rain than any island I’ve ever been to.
Text.LocalizedString: Coral Island has more rain than any island I’ve ever been to.

Text.SourceString: Oh, I’ve been to plenty of islands!//<portrait=normal>I’ve been around, you know. What’s the point of being young if you don’t travel?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, I’ve been to plenty of islands!//<portrait=normal>I’ve been around, you know. What’s the point of being young if you don’t travel?

Text.SourceString: Jeez, I can’t even get fresh air out here without taking in a mouthful of water.//<portrait=concerned>Is this how fish feel?
Text.LocalizedString: Jeez, I can’t even get fresh air out here without taking in a mouthful of water.//<portrait=concerned>Is this how fish feel?

Text.SourceString: Jeez, I can’t even get fresh air out here without taking in a mouthful of water.//<portrait=concerned>Is this how fish feel?
Text.LocalizedString: Jeez, I can’t even get fresh air out here without taking in a mouthful of water.//<portrait=concerned>Is this how fish feel?

Text.SourceString: Hello? Is that you, <PlayerName>$Player</>? I can hear you, but I can’t see through all this rain!
Text.LocalizedString: Hello? Is that you, <PlayerName>$Player</>? I can hear you, but I can’t see through all this rain!

Text.SourceString: I need to cover up my artifacts.//<portrait=sad>Or else all the humidity is going to make them rust.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to cover up my artifacts.//<portrait=sad>Or else all the humidity is going to make them rust.

Text.SourceString: The rain is really coming down out there. I hope it doesn’t ruin your plans for the day.
Text.LocalizedString: The rain is really coming down out there. I hope it doesn’t ruin your plans for the day.

Text.SourceString: I can’t believe it’s raining again. I thought we were supposed to have nice weather this week.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t believe it’s raining again. I thought we were supposed to have nice weather this week.

Text.SourceString: I was going to go down to the pier today, but the rain wouldn’t let up.//<portrait=happy>Oh well! At least I get to see you.
Text.LocalizedString: I was going to go down to the pier today, but the rain wouldn’t let up.//<portrait=happy>Oh well! At least I get to see you.

Text.SourceString: Don’t the big fish come out when it’s raining?//<portrait=happy>I wanna go catch some, but…I’m too lazy.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t the big fish come out when it’s raining?//<portrait=happy>I wanna go catch some, but…I’m too lazy.

Text.SourceString: Rainy days make me feel like curling up with some tea and reading a book… And I don’t even like to read.//<portrait=happy>Weird, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: Rainy days make me feel like curling up with some tea and reading a book… And I don’t even like to read.//<portrait=happy>Weird, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: Think you could surf in weather like this?//<portrait=happy>I bet the waves would be, like, higher than my house.
Text.LocalizedString: Think you could surf in weather like this?//<portrait=happy>I bet the waves would be, like, higher than my house.

Text.SourceString: It better not be raining again tomorrow.//I’ve got things to do.
Text.LocalizedString: It better not be raining again tomorrow.//I’ve got things to do.

Text.SourceString: I hate going into the cavern on days like this.//<portrait=annoyed>Hearing thunder while you’re deep in a cavern tunnel is just too creepy.
Text.LocalizedString: I hate going into the cavern on days like this.//<portrait=annoyed>Hearing thunder while you’re deep in a cavern tunnel is just too creepy.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Charles</> hates when it storms at night. He says he’s worried something will fall on the house.//Worries too much, that one.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Charles</> hates when it storms at night. He says he’s worried something will fall on the house.//Worries too much, that one.

Text.SourceString: I remember this drink my buddies and I came up with, called Stormy Night.//<portrait=happy>Every sip made you roar like a storm!//<portrait=normal>Wanna try it sometime?
Text.LocalizedString: I remember this drink my buddies and I came up with, called Stormy Night.//<portrait=happy>Every sip made you roar like a storm!//<portrait=normal>Wanna try it sometime?

Text.SourceString: I remember this drink my buddies and I came up with, called Stormy Night.//<portrait=happy>Every sip made you roar like the storm!//<portrait=normal>Wanna try it sometime?
Text.LocalizedString: I remember this drink my buddies and I came up with, called Stormy Night.//<portrait=happy>Every sip made you roar like the storm!//<portrait=normal>Wanna try it sometime?

Text.SourceString: Snow day!
Text.LocalizedString: Snow day!

Text.SourceString: The snow makes my hair go flat.//Do you think it looks flat?//<portrait=normal>Phew! Don’t worry about yours. Your hair always looks great!
Text.LocalizedString: The snow makes my hair go flat.//Do you think it looks flat?//<portrait=normal>Phew! Don’t worry about yours. Your hair always looks great!

Text.SourceString: Gold was so valuable in the ancient world.//If they wanted to remember something, they usually immortalized it in gold.
Text.LocalizedString: Gold was so valuable in the ancient world.//If they wanted to remember something, they usually immortalized it in gold.

Text.SourceString: Here’s a weird question for you.//If you’d lived thousands of years ago, what would you want to leave behind for people to remember you by?
Text.LocalizedString: Here’s a weird question for you.//If you’d lived thousands of years ago, what would you want to leave behind for people to remember you by?

Text.SourceString: For me, I think I’d want to keep a notebook.//<portrait=happy>That way, I could tell future generations what life was like when I was around.//<portrait=normal>It doesn’t really matter, though, since I’m here now.
Text.LocalizedString: For me, I think I’d want to keep a notebook.//<portrait=happy>That way, I could tell future generations what life was like when I was around.//<portrait=normal>It doesn’t really matter, though, since I’m here now.

Text.SourceString: Welcome to party central! Make yourself at home.//<portrait=normal><NPCName>Charles</> might disagree with that characterization, but hey!
Text.LocalizedString: Welcome to party central! Make yourself at home.//<portrait=normal><NPCName>Charles</> might disagree with that characterization, but hey!

Text.SourceString: I know what you're thinking, and you're not wrong.//That sweet sound you hear is none other than my curated collection of the smoothest jazz tracks, guaranteed to make you feel like you're floating on a cloud of relaxation and pure bliss.
Text.LocalizedString: I know what you're thinking, and you're not wrong.//That sweet sound you hear is none other than my curated collection of the smoothest jazz tracks, guaranteed to make you feel like you're floating on a cloud of relaxation and pure bliss.

Text.SourceString: I keep it going all the time, because let's face it, smooth jazz knows no boundaries.
Text.LocalizedString: I keep it going all the time, because let's face it, smooth jazz knows no boundaries.

Text.SourceString: Rock climbing? Here?//<portrait=concerned>Hmm… I guess you could, if you really wanted to.//<portrait=annoyed>I don’t recommend it, though.
Text.LocalizedString: Rock climbing? Here?//<portrait=concerned>Hmm… I guess you could, if you really wanted to.//<portrait=annoyed>I don’t recommend it, though.

Text.SourceString: Honestly, rock climbing is pretty good preparation for working in a cavern.//<portrait=sad>But it does seem dangerous to do it here.
Text.LocalizedString: Honestly, rock climbing is pretty good preparation for working in a cavern.//<portrait=sad>But it does seem dangerous to do it here.

Text.SourceString: Okay, I have a joke for you. I’ve been wanting to tell you this one ever since I first saw you come into the cavern.
Text.LocalizedString: Okay, I have a joke for you. I’ve been wanting to tell you this one ever since I first saw you come into the cavern.

Text.SourceString: What did the miner say when he walked into the cavern? //<portrait=happy>He said, “Wow, this place <Italic>rocks</>!”//Where’re the laughs?
Text.LocalizedString: What did the miner say when he walked into the cavern? //<portrait=happy>He said, “Wow, this place <Italic>rocks</>!”//Where’re the laughs?

Text.SourceString: Let’s get some more drinks going in here! Next round’s on me!
Text.LocalizedString: Let’s get some more drinks going in here! Next round’s on me!

Text.SourceString: You're about to witness something truly spectacular, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Something so cool, it's yet to be defined.
Text.LocalizedString: You're about to witness something truly spectacular, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Something so cool, it's yet to be defined.

Text.SourceString: I haven't quite figured it out yet, but trust me, it'll be legendary.//Just stay tuned and be prepared to be amazed.
Text.LocalizedString: I haven't quite figured it out yet, but trust me, it'll be legendary.//Just stay tuned and be prepared to be amazed.

Text.SourceString: You might not know this, but I was captain of the billiards team when I was in college.//<portrait=normal>Not to brag, but they called me <NPCName>Scott</> the Pool Master.
Text.LocalizedString: You might not know this, but I was captain of the billiards team when I was in college.//<portrait=normal>Not to brag, but they called me <NPCName>Scott</> the Pool Master.

Text.SourceString: Is there any way to tell if the big fish are out today? They should do a Coral Island fish forecast.
Text.LocalizedString: Is there any way to tell if the big fish are out today? They should do a Coral Island fish forecast.

Text.SourceString: If there's one thing I'm determined to catch, it's a majestic red king arowana.
Text.LocalizedString: If there's one thing I'm determined to catch, it's a majestic red king arowana.

Text.SourceString: It's like the holy grail of fishing, and I won't rest until I have one on my line.//I'll make it happen.
Text.LocalizedString: It's like the holy grail of fishing, and I won't rest until I have one on my line.//I'll make it happen.

Text.SourceString: Let's settle this once and for all, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//A fishing competition between you and me, to see who can reel in the grandest catch.
Text.LocalizedString: Let's settle this once and for all, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//A fishing competition between you and me, to see who can reel in the grandest catch.

Text.SourceString: Honestly, I’d rather be lifting weights or jogging, but yoga’s cool too.
Text.LocalizedString: Honestly, I’d rather be lifting weights or jogging, but yoga’s cool too.

Text.SourceString: Anything that gets me moving is cool with me.
Text.LocalizedString: Anything that gets me moving is cool with me.

Text.SourceString: I have a habit of making assumptions about people, and you know what?//Most of the time, I turn out to be right.
Text.LocalizedString: I have a habit of making assumptions about people, and you know what?//Most of the time, I turn out to be right.

Text.SourceString: People don’t like it when I do that.//<portrait=happy>But hey, I'll try to tone it down and give people a chance to surprise me.
Text.LocalizedString: People don’t like it when I do that.//<portrait=happy>But hey, I'll try to tone it down and give people a chance to surprise me.

Text.SourceString: I must admit, <PlayerName>$Player</>, for a farmer, you're pretty cool. Heh heh!
Text.LocalizedString: I must admit, <PlayerName>$Player</>, for a farmer, you're pretty cool. Heh heh!

Text.SourceString: Just teasing, <PlayerName>$Player</>. You're pretty cool, <Italic>period</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Just teasing, <PlayerName>$Player</>. You're pretty cool, <Italic>period</>.

Text.SourceString: I feel bad sometimes when I go home and see <NpcName>Charles</> eating alone…//<portrait=sad>He doesn’t really get any visitors.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel bad sometimes when I go home and see <NpcName>Charles</> eating alone…//<portrait=sad>He doesn’t really get any visitors.

Text.SourceString: I mean, I don't exactly have a line of friends waiting at my doorstep either.//<portrait=sad>Guess we're in the same boat, but something about <NpcName>Charles</> tugs at my heartstrings.
Text.LocalizedString: I mean, I don't exactly have a line of friends waiting at my doorstep either.//<portrait=sad>Guess we're in the same boat, but something about <NpcName>Charles</> tugs at my heartstrings.

Text.SourceString: I haven’t personally worked with <NpcName>Zarah</>, but she did donate some of the valuable artifacts at the museum.
Text.LocalizedString: I haven’t personally worked with <NpcName>Zarah</>, but she did donate some of the valuable artifacts at the museum.

Text.SourceString: I often run into her in the forest.//I think she knows a lot more about this island than most of us.
Text.LocalizedString: I often run into her in the forest.//I think she knows a lot more about this island than most of us.

Text.SourceString: Strange, there was a kite just outside my window this morning.
Text.LocalizedString: Strange, there was a kite just outside my window this morning.

Text.SourceString: I haven’t seen anyone flying a kite in ages.
Text.LocalizedString: I haven’t seen anyone flying a kite in ages.

Text.SourceString: I ran into a monster in the cavern the other day and somehow managed to kill it.//<NpcName>Kira</> actually gave me a bounty for it! I wonder if I can do it again?
Text.LocalizedString: I ran into a monster in the cavern the other day and somehow managed to kill it.//<NpcName>Kira</> actually gave me a bounty for it! I wonder if I can do it again?

Text.SourceString: I’m not giving up, though. After all, I’m down in the cavern anyway. Why not make the most of it?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not giving up, though. After all, I’m down in the cavern anyway. Why not make the most of it?

Text.SourceString: Bleh… I had some fresh veggies yesterday, and I can still taste the bitter flavor on my tongue.//<portrait=annoyed>Vegetables aren’t for me. So when I go down in the cavern, I usually just pack vitamins from the clinic.
Text.LocalizedString: Bleh… I had some fresh veggies yesterday, and I can still taste the bitter flavor on my tongue.//<portrait=annoyed>Vegetables aren’t for me. So when I go down in the cavern, I usually just pack vitamins from the clinic.

Text.SourceString: Okra’s all right, though.
Text.LocalizedString: Okra’s all right, though.

Text.SourceString: You’re so chill, like wow!
Text.LocalizedString: You’re so chill, like wow!

Text.SourceString: Very cool. You need to teach me how to be cool like you one of these days!
Text.LocalizedString: Very cool. You need to teach me how to be cool like you one of these days!

Text.SourceString: It might not be a bad idea to move out of <NpcName>Charles’s</> and stay at the inn.//<portrait=normal>Could be a refreshing change of scenery.
Text.LocalizedString: It might not be a bad idea to move out of <NpcName>Charles’s</> and stay at the inn.//<portrait=normal>Could be a refreshing change of scenery.

Text.SourceString: But that’s probably just my weekend brain talking.//<portrait=happy>Who am I kidding? Nothing beats living ten minutes away from work.
Text.LocalizedString: But that’s probably just my weekend brain talking.//<portrait=happy>Who am I kidding? Nothing beats living ten minutes away from work.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been making fake files and slipping them into <NpcName>Charles’s</> work files.//<portrait=normal>I made fake patient files with phony illnesses, like unicorn headaches. I wonder if he’ll catch on. Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been making fake files and slipping them into <NpcName>Charles’s</> work files.//<portrait=normal>I made fake patient files with phony illnesses, like unicorn headaches. I wonder if he’ll catch on. Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: You’re right. I do have too much time on my hands.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re right. I do have too much time on my hands.

Text.SourceString: You know what, <PlayerName>$Player</>? You’re a cool, fun person.//We need to hang out more.
Text.LocalizedString: You know what, <PlayerName>$Player</>? You’re a cool, fun person.//We need to hang out more.

Text.SourceString: Ha ha… That was random. But I just thought you should know.
Text.LocalizedString: Ha ha… That was random. But I just thought you should know.

Text.SourceString: I hope you don’t think I’m a clown or anything.//I know I can be full of it sometimes, but trust me, there’s more to me than that.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope you don’t think I’m a clown or anything.//I know I can be full of it sometimes, but trust me, there’s more to me than that.

Text.SourceString: I care what you think of me.
Text.LocalizedString: I care what you think of me.

Text.SourceString: I’m not stressed about growing old. But… I’m kind of worried I might have to do it alone.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not stressed about growing old. But… I’m kind of worried I might have to do it alone.

Text.SourceString: I know I complain about <NpcName>Charles</> sometimes, but I’d miss him if he ever decided to move on.//<portrait=concerned>I should stop trolling him…//<portrait=happy>Nah! Ha ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: I know I complain about <NpcName>Charles</> sometimes, but I’d miss him if he ever decided to move on.//<portrait=concerned>I should stop trolling him…//<portrait=happy>Nah! Ha ha ha!

Text.SourceString: You sure know how to work the room, huh?//You killed it at that party with <NpcName>Pablo</> and my friends.
Text.LocalizedString: You sure know how to work the room, huh?//You killed it at that party with <NpcName>Pablo</> and my friends.

Text.SourceString: That’s it, <PlayerName>$Player</>! From now on, I’m taking you to all my parties.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s it, <PlayerName>$Player</>! From now on, I’m taking you to all my parties.

Text.SourceString: I’ve thought about changing my hair a couple of times, but I have no idea how to settle on a style.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve thought about changing my hair a couple of times, but I have no idea how to settle on a style.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I could try a buzz cut like <NpcName>Sam</>.//<portrait=normal>It looks good on him, don’t you think? And I’d save a ton on hair gel.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I could try a buzz cut like <NpcName>Sam</>.//<portrait=normal>It looks good on him, don’t you think? And I’d save a ton on hair gel.

Text.SourceString: That’s it, <PlayerName>$Player</>! From now on, I’m taking you to all my parties.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s it, <PlayerName>$Player</>! From now on, I’m taking you to all my parties.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, that’s why I prefer to live in the moment. We have a lot in common.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, that’s why I prefer to live in the moment. We have a lot in common.

Special.SourceString: Yeah, it gets overwhelming after a while.
Special.LocalizedString: Yeah, it gets overwhelming after a while.

Text.SourceString: You know, I couldn’t stop thinking about you last night. Umm…
Text.LocalizedString: You know, I couldn’t stop thinking about you last night. Umm…

Special.SourceString: More than ever, lately… And you’re in it.
Special.LocalizedString: More than ever, lately… And you’re in it.

Text.SourceString: Hear, hear!
Text.LocalizedString: Hear, hear!

Special.SourceString: No. Live in the moment, Scott.
Special.LocalizedString: No. Live in the moment, Scott.

Text.SourceString: If you’re ever feeling down, remember this: everyone’s good at something.//If you haven’t figured out what that is, keep looking, because it’s out there.
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re ever feeling down, remember this: everyone’s good at something.//If you haven’t figured out what that is, keep looking, because it’s out there.

Text.SourceString: Phew! Me, sharing wisdom! That was weird.//<portrait=normal>I guess living with <NpcName>Charles</> has had an effect on me…a good one, it seems.
Text.LocalizedString: Phew! Me, sharing wisdom! That was weird.//<portrait=normal>I guess living with <NpcName>Charles</> has had an effect on me…a good one, it seems.

Text.SourceString: I wish I’d spent the weekend with you instead. It was good, but I know it could’ve been better.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish I’d spent the weekend with you instead. It was good, but I know it could’ve been better.

Text.SourceString: It’s impossible to be bored when I’m hanging out with you… Hear me? Impossible.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s impossible to be bored when I’m hanging out with you… Hear me? Impossible.

Text.SourceString: Well… We all need money, but all joking aside, <PlayerName>$Player</>, don’t take life too seriously. Remember to breathe a little.
Text.LocalizedString: Well… We all need money, but all joking aside, <PlayerName>$Player</>, don’t take life too seriously. Remember to breathe a little.

Text.SourceString: I should really cut my hair, huh?//It seems like the Summer heat bewitches my hair and makes it grow extra fast.
Text.LocalizedString: I should really cut my hair, huh?//It seems like the Summer heat bewitches my hair and makes it grow extra fast.

Text.SourceString: It must get lonely up there at the farm…alone.//<portrait=happy>If you want some company, drop by the house anytime…
Text.LocalizedString: It must get lonely up there at the farm…alone.//<portrait=happy>If you want some company, drop by the house anytime…

Text.SourceString: You’re always welcome at my place.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re always welcome at my place.

Text.SourceString: I think I ate something bad this morning.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I ate something bad this morning.

Text.SourceString: My stomach won’t stop growling. Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: My stomach won’t stop growling. Hmm…

Text.SourceString: I don’t want to show up at your place unannounced. I know you value your privacy, and I like that about you.//<portrait=blushing>But please don’t think I don’t want to.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t want to show up at your place unannounced. I know you value your privacy, and I like that about you.//<portrait=blushing>But please don’t think I don’t want to.

Text.SourceString: Just wanted to clear that up…
Text.LocalizedString: Just wanted to clear that up…

Text.SourceString: The system at the museum was down the other day. Thankfully, <NpcName>Lily</> was able to stop by and help out.
Text.LocalizedString: The system at the museum was down the other day. Thankfully, <NpcName>Lily</> was able to stop by and help out.

Text.SourceString: I could have tried to fix it, I guess.//<portrait=happy>But I didn’t know how… Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: I could have tried to fix it, I guess.//<portrait=happy>But I didn’t know how… Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: I’m liking that shirt on you, <PlayerName>$Player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m liking that shirt on you, <PlayerName>$Player</>!

Text.SourceString: Maybe I’d look good in that color too. I might try it out.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I’d look good in that color too. I might try it out.

Text.SourceString: I was thinking about you last night.//I had my warm milk in bed, and of all a sudden, I remembered the first time I saw you…that Spring, remember?
Text.LocalizedString: I was thinking about you last night.//I had my warm milk in bed, and of all a sudden, I remembered the first time I saw you…that Spring, remember?

Text.SourceString: I thought you were really cute, and you seemed cool from the start.//<portrait=blushing>The rest was just you proving me right.
Text.LocalizedString: I thought you were really cute, and you seemed cool from the start.//<portrait=blushing>The rest was just you proving me right.

Text.SourceString: The rain makes everything feel so fresh and clean. I love the smell of wet pavement and leaves.
Text.LocalizedString: The rain makes everything feel so fresh and clean. I love the smell of wet pavement and leaves.

Text.SourceString: What did you do today, <PlayerName>$Player</>?//<portrait=sad>You seem a little tired. Is it the weather?
Text.LocalizedString: What did you do today, <PlayerName>$Player</>?//<portrait=sad>You seem a little tired. Is it the weather?

Text.SourceString: It seems like the perfect weather for snuggling, don’t you think?
Text.LocalizedString: It seems like the perfect weather for snuggling, don’t you think?

Text.SourceString: I was just thinking about you.
Text.LocalizedString: I was just thinking about you.

Text.SourceString: Go somewhere and warm up, <PlayerName>$Player</>. You look like you’re freezing.
Text.LocalizedString: Go somewhere and warm up, <PlayerName>$Player</>. You look like you’re freezing.

Text.SourceString: Don’t get sick, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t get sick, okay?

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, I wish I’d been born a hundred years ago, when men still wore suits everywhere and jazz was the big thing.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, I wish I’d been born a hundred years ago, when men still wore suits everywhere and jazz was the big thing.

Text.SourceString: Technology is cool and all, but nothing beats a good big-band show.
